The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Suri, Aug. 3: A Class XI student of Beniamadhab High School here today slapped his teacher for not allowing him to attend class.

 Sheikh Ramiz was late and was not in uniform, which is why Dilip Mondal refused to let him enter the classroom. The boys parents have been asked to collect his transfer certificate tomorrow. 

 Calcutta: Newspaper vendors have decided not to participate in the Left-sponsored nation-wide strike on Wednesday following a request from CPM state secretary Biman Bose. Although we support the strike, we shall not join it, Prabhat Chatterjee, the secretary of the West Bengal Newspaper Sellers Samity, said.

 Tamluk: Haradhan Sit, 40, and his father Kangal, were killed when their motorcycle crashed against a sta- tionary bus in Haldia on Friday evening. Police said Haradhan, who was riding the motorcycle, was talking on the mobile phone and spotted the bus late.




